Using the HP Operation "Generate Run URL" to determine HistoryID

Author\: Andy Roth

Inputs are the out of the box inputs for variablename and display text.

Result\: historyId - this is a regex (\d+$) filtered result to pull historyId from URL

d2c5f501-c6b5-494a-baf8-5429b5548354.145cda7d-6d67-47d1-89ef-fe409c62e5eb.description=
Synopsis

    This operator removes duplicate strings from a list of delimited strings.

Inputs

    list - A delimited list of strings (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    delimiter - A sequence of one or more characters used to specify a boundary in a data stream (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: Comma (,).

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case a duplicate string removal, where applicable.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
